          "name": "Pain Sensitivity",
          "subtype": "ability",
          "text": "When a trighoul's tentacle is severed, it becomes stunned 1. Its Speed is reduced by 15 feet until the tentacle is regrown.",
          "type": "stat_block_section"
        },
        {
          "ability_type": "automatic",
          "name": "Tentacle Regrowth",
          "subtype": "ability",
          "text": "A trighoul ordinarily has three tentacles. A creature can attempt to sever a tentacle by specifically targeting it and dealing damage equal to the tentacle's Hit Points. A tentacle that isn't severed completely returns to full Hit Points at the end of any creature's turn. A severed trighoul tentacles regrows, restored to full Hit Points, after 1d4 rounds.",
          "type": "stat_block_section"
        }
      ],
